text:
<@U026PHQ3J>: This feels like the perfect summary of our conversations about the Steelers…
>Sure they have bad years, like any team, but they never seem to be down for long. Even last year, losing to teams like the Browns, Tampa Bay, and the Jets—we'll get to that—they still managed to top their division with 11 wins. Much to the dismay of everyone outside of Yinzerdelphia, the Steelers are a pretty solid franchise.

attachments.text: The Pittsburgh Steelers were, and generally always are, a good football team last year. Still they managed to lose to the Jets.
